        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Well Ive got a bit of an update on this. It seems to be getting worse. I had one beggar the other day who just would not take no for an answer. I dont know if he just didnt speak english or what, but I was getting "pp plz" from this asshole every five minutes for about 4 hours. I kept telling him to go outside and kill stuff to earn cash. He didnt want to.</P><P>Damn what is wrong with these people. The most I have ever blindly asked for from anyone is advice, or for a rez (which I pay for). I dont mind helping Noobs out, If they are nice and pleasant about it I will usually give them 5pp or so, which is enough to get their level 1-4 spells. Its a cheap helping hand. But on the whole they havent even beenm out into the forest to even start killing. They have made a level 1 toon and start begging from the first hi level they see.</P><P>I got talking to one toon (about 11th) the other day, he was asking me where I got my stuff, about the spells and how they work, tactics etc. Now this stuff I dont mind chatting about and will happily give advice to a young nec. After an hour or so, he said he was negotiating to buy a robe at the same time as chatting to me, but he was 50pp short. He had saved about 30pp at 11th, now thats not bad, so i gave him the 50pp. After another 6-7 Mrak/Jacker/Other troll whose name I can never remember, kills I had it back anyway.</P><P>At the same time I was doing a transfer to another toon. She gave me a bunch of gear and some cash (i didnt notice the cash) I returned the gear and she said wears the cash, I checked and found I had a bunch of GP and SP I didnt have before so I knew she had given me something.  I asked how much she had given me and she gave me an exact amount like 56pp, 18gp, 12sp,5 cp sort of thing.</P><P>So I think thats cool, give her 60pp and shes happy. We had been doing this in /say, a nearby newbie says can I have some Pp plz?. Im feeling generous so I give him 5pp (enough to buy spells etc) he doesnt accept, so i /tell him hit accept, I have to go, he says wheres the rest?. Im like What are you talking about?. He replies "you said 56pp, wheres the rest?". I cancelled the trade and gated.</P><P>For the next hour hes bugging me, "Whats that robe?, Can you give it to me so i can see what it looks like on?". Now I wear a Warlocks. 1. its NODROP, 2. Like I am going to give a level one newb something like a Warlocks robe to "try on". Is this guy kidding or what?. Next its "where did you get it?, how can I get one?." So I tell him, goto Kael Drakkal, get a VERY VERY rare drop off a level 55+ giant, acquire 3 Pristine emeralds, run to Thurg and hand it all in for you Robe.</P><P>Q."Can you help me do that". Okay so hes a nut. <BR>Q."Where are you going?"<BR>A."Dragon Necropolis"<BR>Q."Wheres that?"<BR>A."get a port to Cobalt Scar, Run to Sirens Grotto, run thru SG to get to Western Wastes, run thru there to DN."<BR>Q."Can you help me get there?"</P><P>AAARGH. Am I just too nice?</P><P>58 DE Necromancer<BR><br><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=49001" target="_blank">Profile</a><BR><a href="http://sizzlesites.com/Ulaa/" target="_blank">Ulaa's web site</a><br><BR><img src="http://www.sizzlesites.com/Ulaa/sig.jpg" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
